def: The ramie or grass-cloth plant. See Grass-cloth plant, underGrass.
A kind of wash bottle with two or three necks; -- so calledafter the inventor, Peter Woulfe, an English chemist.
Of or pertaining to the tonsils; tonsilitic. [Written alsotonsillar.]
Furnished with tusks.The tusked boar out of the wood. Milton.
The qualities of a father; parantal kindness, care, etc.
To find again; to get or experience again. Sandys.
Situated under or inside a sheath or vaginal membrane; as, thesubvaginal, or subdural, spaces about the optic nerve.
To invest with dignity or honor; to make illustrious; to givedistinction to; to exalt in rank; to honor.Your worth will dignity our feast. B. Jonson.
Like a mob; tumultuous; lawless; as, a mobbish act. Bp. Kent.
